ì whether it‚Äôs making your code more asynchronous, moving it to the background, or sharing data across concurrent tasks."}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25":{"kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25","abstract":[{"text":"Xcode 26, Swift 6.2, iOS\/macOS\/tvOS\/visionOS 26.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"New APIs: ","type":"text"},{"code":"Foundation Models","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AlarmKit"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PermissionKit"},{"type":"text","text":", and more."}],"images":[{"identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"WWDC25.jpg","type":"card"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25","type":"topic","title":"WWDC25"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-270-Codealong-Elevate-an-app-with-Swift-concurrency":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-270-Codealong-Elevate-an-app-with-Swift-concurrency","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to optimize your app‚Äôs user experience with Swift concurrency as we update an existing sample app. We‚Äôll start with a main-actor app, then gradually introduce asynchronous code as we need to. We‚Äôll use tasks to optimize code running on the main actor, and discover how to parallelize code by offloading work to the background. We‚Äôll explore what data-race safety provides, and work through interpreting and fixing data-race safety errors. Finally, we‚Äôll show how you can make the most out of structured concurrency in the context of an app."}],"title":"Code-along: Elevate an app with Swift concurrency","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-270-codealong-elevate-an-app-with-swift-concurrency","type":"topic"